reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Standup Desk
reviews.reviewText: I desperately needed a good desk. Preferably a standup desk. We all know how expensive these things are and quality definitely drops with the price.After a lot of researching and hair pulling, I went with this Fezibo. I was pretty excited when it arrived. It was in a much smaller box than I had imagined, but that was no problem.I found it fairly easy to assemble, but ran into one snag. The bar(spit) that spins to raise/lower the table seemed to not fit right. I got in touch with customer service where I explained my situation and sent photos. They were quick to ask pertinent questions, but could not help other than ask for a day to examine and they would send me a new part.Luckily, that's when my wife interceded and pointed out I had tried to incorrectly mount the part. It was my fault. I quickly put it together and all was good. I let customer service know and all were happy.The desk looks great. Works great. Is quite sturdy and fits into my small area nicely. I am quite pleased with this purchase for its quality and price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble, well packaged, good value
reviews.reviewText: I was impressed with how well it was packaged. All hardware was in individual bags, labeled with letters or numbers to correspond to the assembly directions. There was foam around every piece so despite the outside box being a little beat-up, all parts were flawless. For most of the small hardware like screws, there was at least one extra leftover.The assembly was pretty straightforward and easy to follow. It took me about an hour to assemble by myself. After you attach the legs to the table top, you do have to flip it which would be easier with two people but it's not terribly heavy so it's doable by yourself.For the space I have available, the 55" fits perfectly and has room for both of my laptops and an extra monitor. I will probably look into adding monitor arms to get another monitor to fit. Feels pretty sturdy despite the top being pretty thin. There is a very slight wobble if you bump it when it's at its highest setting but doesn't seem like it would tip over.The control panel has 3 presets and is easy to set them, simple press the "S" button while on the desired height and then tap the 1, 2, or 3 button to set that button to that height. The three presets allow you to set a sitting height, standing height and another height that I use for when I'm on the standing board which bumps me up another inch or two. I am about 5'11" and with the standing board I have to have the desk maxed out so if you're much taller, it might not be high enough for you. The motor is not silent but isn't very loud.For the price, it is well worth it. Looked into some others and they were 3-4x as expensive as this for a similarly sized desk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No need to pay more -- This desk is great
reviews.reviewText: Easy to assemble. The desk is sturdy and doesn't shake. Power control works well but you need to reset it befor it will work. Easy enough, hold "up" and "down" together.I got this not so much as a standing desk, but because I'm tall and want a higher desk surface. This fits the bill perfectly as the control moves the top up and down smoothly and can store 3 positions.The desk top is in two pieces that need to be edge joined with dowls. This gives a seem down the middle of the top which may be annoying to some. It would bother me. Instead I got the seriously ugly rustic brown color at a significant discount, probably because nobody wants it. The top went straight to the trash and I'm using the 24x48 top I used previously with fixed legs. I suggest this route as I have no seem and a surface I like.The only negative other than the seem in the top, is that with the 24x48 size that I got, the legs are not at the left and right edges. They are set in about 6 inches on each side. The reason I assume, is so they can use the same legs with a smaller top. They're not close enough to be annoying so it isn't much of an issue.Overall, I'm very happy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great standing desk! *UPDATE*
reviews.reviewText: UPDATE: I've had this desk for almost a year. The desk itself has held up very nicely. BUT, the motor is an issue. Still seems to work fine when going up. Going down however, it always goes down a bit, stops, goes up a bit, then stops. This is true with both the presets and the down button. So you have to press either button repeatedly to get it back to the original position. This happens every single time. Still glad I didn't pay hundred even thousands of dollars for an expensive standing desk lol, but it is somewhat annoying.*********************************I researched standing desk and was almost convinced by various articles, forums, etc. that I needed to spend several hundred dollars for a good standing desk. Then I decided to buy this one for a fraction of the cost to try out for a while to see if I would actually use it before investing that much.I love this desk! It was easy to assemble by myself, it's the perfect size, it has the four memory presents, the motor runs smoothly and it's sturdy. I don't notice any wobbling when I'm using it in a standing mode. I also love how it looks, the rustic brown is so pretty and I don't even notice the split top (something I was worried about). I am super happy with this desk, and don't see the need to spend 2-3x more. Highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High-quality adjustable desk and at a good price!
reviews.reviewText: This is the second Fezibo adjustable desk I have purchased for our office, the first was for me. I've had mine for about 10 months now and I am very happy with it. Sturdy, convenient (electric set heights), and nice looking. I paired it with the Mountup dual monitor desk mount arm and both (desk and monitor arm) being sturdy, my two screens do not wobble! I'm a happy camper!

Great quality, great value, better than whatever is sold in in-person stores! Also easy to assemble as everything was labeled clearly. You may need a drill for when you have to screw the legs into the desk. It was quite the arm workout!

reviews.reviewTitle: Correct. Vigilance sur Couleur et dimensions
reviews.reviewText: Le mécanisme est bon rapport qualité prix.La stabilité est bonne.Le plateau du bureau fait 160 x 60/75, et pas 70/75cm. Sur le descriptif, les dimensions sont pas correctes, en cours de correction par le vendeur.J’ai commandé le plus clair. Attention à la photo sur le site, le bureau est bien plus foncé en réalité, avec des reflets orangés.Facile à monter.Vendeur à l’écoute.

La scrivania è arrivata in un imballaggio chiuso e senza apparenti danni, ma le tavole in legno presentavano un'ammaccatura sulla facciata superiore e un'altra in uno degli angoli (ho risolto applicando dello stucco).Non è molto stabile (oscilla), soprattutto dagli 80 cm a salire.Diciamo che per ciò che mi serve (studio/lavoro) e per il prezzo pagato va più che bene (è assurdo pagare per una scrivania regolabile in altezza dai 300€ a salire).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Perfect Desk at a Reasonable Price
reviews.reviewText: I needed a proper desk and was hesitant to spend hundreds on a standing desk, unsure if I would use all the features. I looked at many options and this one seemed the best value and had decent reviews. However, at the price I still thought it may be too good to be true and felt it was a gamble to purchase. I was worried about it wobbling, or not looking like the photos. I needn't have worried. Husband assembled it in an hour or so and it looks great. Best of all, it is easy to use and very sturdy. We didn't do any extra gluing or enhancement. Simply followed the instructions. Its easy to preset the heights, smooth to adjust, and is steady to work at when standing. I love this desk and so glad I purchased. Its as good as the much more expensive desks in my work's office. I wouldn't hesitate to recommend
